# Test exports-based self-references with lazy indexing AND recursion disabled
# (-index=lazy -r=false lib/pkg). Only //lib/pkg is (re)generated; every other
# package keeps its committed BUILD file and is only reached if //lib/pkg asks
# gazelle to lazily index it.
#
# The npm_package target is disabled (see lib/pkg/BUILD.in) so the
# self-references are resolved purely from the source ts_project. Under lazy
# indexing the "@lib/pkg/sub" and "@lib/pkg/feat/*" target directories
# (lib/pkg/sub, lib/pkg/feat) are only indexed when //lib/pkg declares them in
# GenerateResult.RelsToIndex, so resolution must expand the package.json
# "exports" targets into rels-to-index (tsPackageInfoToRelsToIndex). Without
# that the self-references mis-resolve to the package's own npm link
# (//:node_modules/@lib/pkg), a circular dependency.
# https://nodejs.org/api/packages.html#self-referencing-a-package-using-its-name
#
#  * "@lib/pkg/sub" -> ./sub/main.js resolves to //lib/pkg/sub
#  * "@lib/pkg/feat/x" matches the "./feat/*" pattern -> //lib/pkg/feat
workspace(name = "pnpm_workspace_exports_lazy_norecurse")
